# @types

## Overview

This directory contains TypeScript declaration files (`.d.ts`) that extend and augment type definitions for external libraries. TypeScript automatically detects type definitions in this special `@types` folder.

## Purpose

- **Type extension**: Extends existing module types without modifying their source code
- **Enhanced intellisense**: Provides autocompletion and type checking for library interfaces
- **Custom configurations**: Tailors library typings to match project-specific requirements